  <div class="container">
    <h1>HELLO WORLD!</h1>
    <h2>Express / EJS / Serverless / Netlify</h2>
    <img src="images/gifkitty.gif" alt="kitty" />
    <div class="list">
      <ul>
        <li><span>Server Configuration:</span>
          <ul>
            <li>server.js uses serverless-http to wrap the Express app for serverless deployment.</li>
            <li>app.js sets up the Express app, configures EJS as the view engine, serves static files, and defines a
              route for rendering the index.ejs template.</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li><span>Netlify Configuration:</span>
          <ul>
            <li>netlify.toml specifies build command, functions directory, and included files. It defines redirect rules
              for images, CSS, and all other requests to the serverless function.</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li><span>View Templates:</span>
          <ul>
            <li>index.ejs is an EJS template that renders an HTML page with a title, CSS styles, and an image.</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li><span>Package Configuration:</span>
          <ul>
            <li>package.json lists project dependencies and provides metadata about the project.</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
